# VPN_SWITCH_DNS_openvpn - OpenVPN DNS server
#
# Default DNS server for OpenVPN connections.
# This follows the VPN_SWITCH_DNS_<protocol> naming convention for
# protocol-agnostic DNS server lookup.
#
# Default: 10.96.0.1 (VPN provider OpenVPN gateway)
#
# VPN provider's OpenVPN service assigns IPs from 10.96.0.0/16 with gateway at .1
# This DNS server is used when the OpenVPN server doesn't push DNS via dhcp-option.
#
# Behavior:
#   - Used as fallback if config doesn't contain dhcp-option DNS directives
#   - Can be overridden per-database via setenv command
#   - Configured via resolvconf and requires local_unbound reload
